T1  - Expected Uncertain Utility Theory
AU  - Gul, Faruk
AU  - Pesendorfer, Wolfgang
Y1  - 2014/01/01
PY  - 2014
DA  - 2014/01/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA9188
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1
EP  - 39
VL  - 82
IS  - 1
KW  - Ambiguity
KW  - Ellsberg
KW  - subjective probability
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA9188
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We introduce and analyze expected uncertain utility (EUU) theory. A prior and an interval utility characterize an EUU decision maker. The decision maker transforms each uncertain prospect into an interval-valued prospect that assigns an interval of prizes to each state. She then ranks prospects according to their expected interval utilities. We define uncertainty aversion for EUU, use the EUU model to address the Ellsberg Paradox and other ambiguity evidence, and relate EUU theory to existing models.
ER  - 

